title: Two natural products from the seeds ofCitrus reticulataBlanco (Rutaceae) inhibit estrogen biosynthesis by regulating the PI3K-aromatase pathway.
abstract: The seeds of Citrus reticulata Blanco (Rutaceae) (SCR), a traditional Chinese medicine derived from Citrus, is known for its diverse bioactivities, including potential anti-breast cancer effects, but the mechanism of action remains unclear.
